 JOHANNESBURG - He flew the South African flag high in the US and scooped a Grammy, and now Black Coffee is officially back home for what will probably be a week-long celebration . Meanwhile, the congratulatory messages for this South African first have been pouring in. His album 'Subconsciously' was named Best Dance or Electronic Album at the 64th Grammy Awards in Las Vegas. He beat Sylvan Esso, Illenium, Major Lazer, Ten City, and Marshmello to scoop the award. Black Coffee is the first African DJ to receive the accolade, adding to his BET Award.